like usual.

322
00:22:25,024 --> 00:22:27,998
He feels good, just had
his physical at Walter Reed,

323
00:22:27,999 --> 00:22:30,227
everything checked out
just fine,

324
00:22:30,379 --> 00:22:32,130
and, all of a sudden,

325
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:35,001
he's walking away from
the U.S. Senate. Mmm?

326
00:22:35,002 --> 00:22:36,948
This means that
Mr. St. John loses...

327
00:22:36,949 --> 00:22:39,620
...one of his "A" clients.

328
00:22:40,444 --> 00:22:43,244
How's our boy?
Have you seen him lately?

329
00:22:43,406 --> 00:22:44,979
I called him,
he's in South America.

330
00:22:44,980 --> 00:22:46,952
He was doing the...

331
00:22:46,953 --> 00:22:49,880
...presidential campaign
last week, there.

332
00:22:50,258 --> 00:22:52,058
Are you two getting
back together?

333
00:22:53,416 --> 00:22:55,416
- Are you?
- No.

334
00:22:55,763 --> 00:22:57,363
Let's get right to it, shall we?

335
00:22:57,538 --> 00:23:00,038
Did he screw you
as good as he did me?

336
00:23:01,903 --> 00:23:04,103
- Have you seen him?
- No.

337
00:23:04,510 --> 00:23:07,110
You're doing the New Mexico
gubernatorial race, uh...

338
00:23:07,391 --> 00:23:09,391
- ...Frank McKusker, right?
- Yeah.

339
00:23:09,444 --> 00:23:12,044
You'll be seeing him
very soon.

340
00:23:12,692 --> 00:23:16,092
- He got Wallace Furman.
- Yeah, I heard he signed on.

341
00:23:16,334 --> 00:23:18,694
Well, why not? Get the best
money can buy, right?

342
00:23:18,695 --> 00:23:21,000
That's what he is, isn't he?
I mean, he's the very best.

343
00:23:21,001 --> 00:23:24,682
It doesn't matter what or who
gets hurt in the process.

344
00:23:25,627 --> 00:23:28,827
Sometimes I look at him
and he seems the same.

345
00:23:29,354 --> 00:23:31,756
You were married to him,
so tell me,

346
00:23:31,757 --> 00:23:33,257
when did it happen?

347
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,380
<i>I keep thinking back and
I can't figure it out.</i>

348
00:23:38,497 --> 00:23:41,697
When did he start thinking
it didn't matter anymore?

349
00:23:42,874 --> 00:23:44,912
I never heard of this guy.
He's got me on the phone...

350
00:23:44,913 --> 00:23:48,464
...one hour, 55 minutes
after you'd made the calls.

351
00:23:48,564 --> 00:23:52,164
I'm not surprised.
We knew it would get around.

352
00:23:52,978 --> 00:23:54,222
Who is he?

353
00:23:54,223 --> 00:23:56,823
- Billings or Cade?
- Either one.

354
00:23:57,684 --> 00:23:59,984
Well, I've met Billings once.

355
00:24:00,451 --> 00:24:01,951
He's in Washington.

356
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:05,103
I believe he has a
public relations firm,

357
00:24:05,104 --> 00:24:07,050
I'm not exactly sure.

358
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:10,150
And Cade, owns
a number of businesses.

359
00:24:10,906 --> 00:24:14,256
Trucking, bottling,

360
00:24:14,406 --> 00:24:17,906
and something with pipelines,
mostly in the Midwest.

361
00:24:17,965 --> 00:24:21,265
He's made some large contributions
to the State party.

362
00:24:21,382 --> 00:24:23,182
He got a lot of
publicity last year.

363
00:24:23,244 --> 00:24:26,243
He headed a
blue-ribbon commission on...

364
00:24:26,244 --> 00:24:28,144
...governmental waste.

365
00:24:30,746 --> 00:24:32,260
What do you think?

366
00:24:32,410 --> 00:24:34,046
About what?

367
00:24:35,223 --> 00:24:36,523
Cade.

368
00:24:40,876 --> 00:24:42,576
Should I take him on?

369
00:24:42,627 --> 00:24:45,001
Well, I'd give it
some serious thought.

370
00:24:45,002 --> 00:24:46,702
Is that the new draft?

371
00:24:48,788 --> 00:24:51,000
Yeah. Yeah, that's it.

372
00:24:52,838 --> 00:24:55,253
Still, you must be happy about
connecting with McKusker.

373
00:24:55,254 --> 00:24:58,228
- He's the big favorite, right?
- Oh, I sure am, honey.

374
00:24:58,229 --> 00:25:00,429
Gotta look out for
my batting average.

375
00:25:00,832 --> 00:25:03,032
Speak of the devil!
Look at this.

376
00:25:04,380 --> 00:25:06,380
As I live and breathe.

377
00:25:06,717 --> 00:25:07,798
Hello.

378
00:25:07,799 --> 00:25:09,117
Darling.

379
00:25:10,038 --> 00:25:12,538
- I'm sorry about Sam.
- Yeah.

380
00:25:12,971 --> 00:25:14,971
How's Claire taking it?

381
00:25:15,553 --> 00:25:18,003
She's doing fine.
So is he.

382
00:25:18,004 --> 00:25:20,154
Pete, Pete-- um--

383
00:25:21,489 --> 00:25:23,384
Is it-- Is it cancer?

384
00:25:23,385 --> 00:25:25,289
I-I know his physical
last month was good--

385
00:25:25,374 --> 00:25:27,374
His press conference
is at 10:00.

386
00:25:27,804 --> 00:25:29,062
What did he say?

387
00:25:29,212 --> 00:25:32,004
- "His press conference is at 10:00."
- Oh.

388
00:25:34,256 --> 00:25:35,556
Thanks.

389
00:25:38,035 --> 00:25:41,538
I hear we'll be running into
each other around New Mexico.

390
00:25:41,539 --> 00:25:43,735
Yeah. How about we keep it
close till the last week?

391
00:25:43,736 --> 00:25:45,436
Then flip a coin.

392
00:25:46,639 --> 00:25:48,539
I saw you on Brinkley.
It's incredible but I think...

393
00:25:48,540 --> 00:25:50,898
...you're more arrogant
since we got divorced.

394
00:25:50,899 --> 00:25:54,138
Hey, look, don't go
blaming yourself.

395
00:25:57,020 --> 00:26:00,106
You're meeting with
Jerome Cade at 10:30.

396
00:26:00,306 --> 00:26:02,558
- Tonight?
- Look, his people called!

397
00:26:02,559 --> 00:26:04,439
You're going flat out
the rest of the week and...

398
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:07,099
...they wanted this meeting
as soon as possible.

399
00:26:10,054 --> 00:26:11,254
Look,

400
00:26:12,287 --> 00:26:13,822
I'll call back
and postpone.

401
00:26:13,823 --> 00:26:15,687
You don't need to take
this guy on.

402
00:26:15,771 --> 00:26:18,833
Besides Stannard in Seattle,
we still got Cepeda.

403
00:26:18,834 --> 00:26:22,030
And Furman in New Mexico's
gonna take a lot of time.

404
00:26:22,130 --> 00:26:23,630
It's all right.

405
00:26:38,654 --> 00:26:40,975
<i>All right, it boils down
to this, Governor.</i>

406
00:26:40,976 --> 00:26:44,476
We don't wait for Murdoch
to bust our balls, we jump his.

407
00:26:44,735 --> 00:26:46,349
Now, you've seen how
he's braked out.

408
00:26:46,350 --> 00:26:49,650
You're getting killed on
the death penalty veto.

409
00:26:49,843 --> 00:26:53,943
Ever wonder why the Eastwood movies
do so good up here?

410
00:26:54,396 --> 00:26:56,576
And then, there is the--

411
00:26:56,726 --> 00:26:58,796
the divorce.

412
00:26:58,891 --> 00:27:00,291
Not so much that you split up,

413
00:27:00,410 --> 00:27:03,523
...but we had been pushing
the family image...

414
00:27:03,574 --> 00:27:05,010
...in the first campaign.

415
00:27:06,565 --> 00:27:09,022
<i>I read the report
this morning, Pete.</i>

416
00:27:09,023 --> 00:27:10,791
Not unexpected,

417
00:27:10,792 --> 00:27:12,850
but the fact that the resentment
has lasted this long...

418
00:27:12,851 --> 00:27:14,474
...was surprising.

419
00:27:14,475 --> 00:27:17,714
Look, Governor, if you go over
the focus group interview...

420
00:27:17,715 --> 00:27:19,990
you'll see they keep
mentioning the fact...

421
00:27:19,991 --> 00:27:23,021
...that you married
your campaign manager.

422
00:27:26,161 --> 00:27:29,261
They also keep mentioning
that campfire commercial.

423
00:27:30,519 --> 00:27:32,095
Harry cooking eggs
over the fire...

424
00:27:32,096 --> 00:27:34,996
...for the kids, while
you're chopping wood?

425
00:27:35,788 --> 00:27:38,588
That was almost four years ago.
Hell of a spot!

426
00:27:38,646 --> 00:27:42,746
The election's this fall.
I gotta teach you how to cook.

427
00:27:46,563 --> 00:27:48,163
Governor, this is
my recommendation.

428
00:27:48,286 --> 00:27:50,772
We advance the media buys
three weeks,

429
00:27:50,773 --> 00:27:53,815
shift money from the fall schedule
if we have to and blow him away now.

430
00:27:53,816 --> 00:27:56,410
Back him off, before he nails you
for mothering killers and...

431
00:27:56,411 --> 00:28:00,311
- ...dumping Harry and the kids.
- She didn't dump them.

432
00:28:03,622 --> 00:28:06,022
Yeah, anyway,
that's my recommendation.

433
00:28:13,555 --> 00:28:16,955
We've leased 30 minutes
of satellite time.

434
00:28:17,161 --> 00:28:20,461
They'll be beaming him in
in about 90 seconds.

435
00:28:20,554 --> 00:28:24,054
So, let's move our chairs
a little closer.

436
00:28:25,050 --> 00:28:28,050
Charles, go ahead, sit down.
Mrs. Furman.

437
00:28:28,311 --> 00:28:30,611
Put the chairs close
so we can talk into the mic.

